\subsection*{Project synopsis}
\vspace{-2.8ex}

\begin{minipage}[t][2.2in]{0.65\textwidth}
    \vspace{0pt}

    The island of Kinakuta is a tropical island prized for its distinctive
    wildlife, which many tourists travel to see each year. Last year, however,
    changes in the environment upset the complex ecosystem in Kinakuta and
    caused the algae in the inland lakes to proliferate at an abnormally high
    rate. Alarmed that the algae would take over the lake and kill the fish,
    scientists decided to import a special breed of \emph{crappie} known to
    feed on algae. Crappie, however, are not optimally suited to the warm
    tropical temperatures. The imported crappie became infected with a fungus
    that threatens the entire fish population of Kinakuta.

