        \item Although the drug is very certain to be effective, it will take
        time to develop such a large amount of the drug. Experimental trials,
        scaled up to what Kinakuta needs, predict that the lab contracted to
        make the drug will be able to meet demand within 4 months.

    \end{compactitem}

\newpage

    Your team must now pull together all of its ideas to calculate an estimate
    of when the maximum rate of infection will be reached. If the time is
    within the window of effectiveness, you must then find out how many
    crappie the drug program can save. You should report all answers with
    three significant digits. Once you finish your calculations, your team
    should write a professional report restating the problem and summarizing
    your work and your findings. The crappie mission is critical and there's
    no room for mistakes. A rough report just won't do. Thus, your report must
    contain at least one meaningful, carefully labeled graph that adds
    something to the argument your team is making.

